Democratic Change (Spanish: Cambio Democrtico) is a newly formed, center-left political party in El Salvador. It was formed by ex-members of the Christian Democratic Party (PDC), Farabundo Marti National Liberation Front (FMLN), and United Democratic Center (CDU). It is social-christian and social-democratic in orientation, incorporating what the party calls the "democratic left" [1] In the 12 March 2006 legislative election, the party won 3.1% of the popular vote and 2 out of 84 seats. At the January 18, 2009 legislative elections, Democratic Change won 2.1% of the vote and 1 seat. 
